00:13:12.375 --> 00:13:17.700
Child, forget about kind of
friends, family, all of that.

00:13:17.700 --> 00:13:21.580
So those are the sacrifices that
it seems to take because

00:13:21.580 --> 00:13:23.860
you have to work on other
people's schedules.

00:13:23.860 --> 00:13:26.480
And the time zone thing is so
great and the travel time is

00:13:26.480 --> 00:13:30.580
so great that it's pretty hard
to figure out when the factory

00:13:30.580 --> 00:13:32.840
is going to be down in advance,
because you have to

00:13:32.840 --> 00:13:35.860
be there immediately if
there's an issue.

00:13:39.820 --> 00:13:44.340
I suppose disadvantages of our
technology, today we've sort

00:13:44.340 --> 00:13:47.070
of started with lower
front-of-screen performance on

00:13:47.070 --> 00:13:49.200
some level, although
it's more readable.

00:13:49.200 --> 00:13:54.350
Which should matter because
books may disappear, but

00:13:54.350 --> 00:13:58.750
reading is not probably going
to disappear any time soon.

00:13:58.750 --> 00:14:04.630
But Apple communicates with
its customers very well.

00:14:04.630 --> 00:14:08.270
So whatever Apple says matters,
that's what matters.

00:14:08.270 --> 00:14:10.610
Didn't used to be important to
be able to read a screen like

00:14:10.610 --> 00:14:13.160
that, but now it is because
Apple said it was.

00:14:13.160 --> 00:14:16.280
So we all have to do that.

00:14:16.280 --> 00:14:19.440
I'm really grateful that Apple,
a lot of us in the

00:14:19.440 --> 00:14:22.590
display community and hardware
community for a long time

00:14:22.590 --> 00:14:24.040
wanted higher resolution.

00:14:24.040 --> 00:14:27.760
And I always spent the $500
extra to buy something with

00:14:27.760 --> 00:14:28.510
high resolution.

00:14:28.510 --> 00:14:31.530
But now Apple has communicated
effectively to its customers

00:14:31.530 --> 00:14:33.050
that resolution matters,
so everybody

00:14:33.050 --> 00:14:34.100
