00:17:40.030 --> 00:17:42.280
always failed, was the
cooking menu device.

00:17:42.280 --> 00:17:43.455
So maybe this is it.

00:17:43.455 --> 00:17:46.362
But it's an issue.

00:17:46.362 --> 00:17:49.210
JEAN WANG: Well hopefully
with Glass you can

00:17:49.210 --> 00:17:51.900
use Glass for cooking.

00:17:51.900 --> 00:17:55.130
MARY LOU JEPSEN: We're looking
at a world in 2020 where the

00:17:55.130 --> 00:17:57.530
estimates are there will be
10 devices per person.

00:17:57.530 --> 00:18:00.540
And so the charging gets
to be an issue

00:18:00.540 --> 00:18:02.550
because all of the adapters.

00:18:02.550 --> 00:18:05.090
And sure, there's the inductive
charging, but that's

00:18:05.090 --> 00:18:09.360
not very efficient.

00:18:09.360 --> 00:18:14.340
And it'd be nicer, I think, the
reason I work so hard is I

00:18:14.340 --> 00:18:17.820
believe we have to get a world
of self-powered devices.

00:18:17.820 --> 00:18:22.610
Where you have to lower, just
like Intel does, or Qualcomm,

00:18:22.610 --> 00:18:26.490
or any chip maker, in the screen
and everything, the

00:18:26.490 --> 00:18:30.130
power is so low so that it
becomes like a calculator, a

00:18:30.130 --> 00:18:32.320
small little solar
cell is enough to

00:18:32.320 --> 00:18:34.080
power the whole thing.

00:18:34.080 --> 00:18:35.730
And I think that we
can get there.

00:18:35.730 --> 00:18:37.820
Solar cells have gotten
a lot better.

00:18:37.820 --> 00:18:41.570
But the screen power consumption
now takes 90% of

00:18:41.570 --> 00:18:42.840
the battery.

00:18:42.840 --> 00:18:45.860
It's only a small exaggeration
to say the battery in a device

00:18:45.860 --> 00:18:47.830
is there to power the screen.

00:18:47.830 --> 00:18:51.460
And so, I think that that
will open up what

00:18:51.460 --> 00:18:53.650
we can do with things.

00:18:53.650 --> 00:18:58.500
But take it further, why can't
we exhale the device, or spray

00:18:58.500 --> 00:19:01.940
paint it on the wall and peel
